Text.Value: Certainly.
You might want to stop doing them before you kill yourself.
This is incredible. I'm seeing stars!
Leave.
Astarion, we can leave if you don't want to be around her.
Such harsh words for an old friend!
FIRE IN THE - Oh! My silk, what are the chances - it's you!

EditorData.NodeContext:
Looking behind her shoulder after running out of an exploding building (though she's unscathed)

'My silk' as a stand in for 'my stars!' or 'my gods!'
EditorData.logicalname: First time she see us (FIRE ACTIVE)

Text.Value: Is this going to kill me?
I say, I'm positively giddy! Go on - drink the formula!
FIRE IN THE - Oh! My silk, what are the chances - it's you!

EditorData.NodeContext:
Looking behind her shoulder after running out of an exploding building (though she's unscathed)

'My silk' as a stand in for 'my stars!' or 'my gods!'

Text.Value: Lead the way.
Not today. Do you have anything else to trade?
Risky. But - erm - safe!
Exactly. Think of the potential!
You are the world's first detonative exsanguinator. To put it simply: From this day on, your blood goes boom. Big boom! Ahaha! It's incredible!
Naturally, I always ask first. I'm civilised, unlike you.
Ah, my friend. If you've any more blood to spare, I'd be happy to exchange it for something of more use to you.
Oh! My silk, what are the chances - it's you!

EditorData.NodeContext: 'My silk' as a stand in for 'my stars!' or 'my gods!'
EditorData.logicalname: First time she see us (FIRE INACTIVE)

Text.Value: What an odd question.
Oh, that perfect specimen is still travelling with you? And I missed him? What a terrible pity.
Well, not you. But your travel companion. The one with the very special little friend stuck in their brain.
When you first entered this home, you saw the incredible latent power within your blood exposed in all its nuances. Formula Gruna will unleash that power within you.
Do you drink everything any petty mixer places in your hand? You must have a most colourful chamber pot.
You've had enough of my blood.
My research will be quite worthless without proof. And my proof is running through your veins. I only need a tiny bit. Then - then my life will truly begin.
I knew my blood was potent, but I didn't know it could do that.
Now, now. I do think that's enough. When you see what I've been working on, bygones will all be bygones, I assure you.
If that's her 'formula' I can smell, it's even fouler than her blood. Gods below...
I appreciate the thought, but I'm not the person I was the last time we met. And if she can unlock the kind of power she's promising...
Ah - I've already taken of you today; I'm afraid I can only use the first sample of the day. Nevertheless, if there's anything of mine that would be of use to you, do say so.
Now, let me offer you a little treat. In exchange for the teensiest vial of your marvellous blood, I'll give you something that'll really throw your enemies for a loop.
I approve. Any who dare to make me bleed should suffer dire consequences.
Leave.
Forgive the fire and brimstone. Your blood is far more volatile than I'd anticipated.
In due time.
Just as long as she knows who belongs to who this time.
Now now, darling. Let's not be rude...
Fine. Take some then.
Well, death never stopped me before. I don't know why it should now.
Nor have I. No matter how hard I try.
Until next time.
Offer her a vein.
Say no - the only thing she's offering is pain and I don't want to see you hurt.
But! We have quite a bit to discuss. What a wonder you came to my door just when you did.
That's terrifying.
What are you doing? That had better go down the drain and not down your gullet.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player just accepted a disgusting/dangerous drink

Text.Value: I'll only ask a nominal fee in exchange.
Until next time.
You seem surprised. Had you expected me to die?
Nervous to see me again, is he? How sweet.
All right. Hand it over.
Astarion, we can leave if you don't want to be around her.
Oh my - my heavens! You LIVED!
I destroyed it.
There are other necks available for biting, of course. If you were so inclined.
I appreciate the thought, truly, but if this is something you want to look into...
YES! That is - do follow me.
Still, I have other items that might interest you.
Oblodra - the blood merchant. I hadn't hoped to meet you again.
Just a look. And if we don't like what we see, we can always kill her later.
Oh, I can only offer my consolation. And say to you, pretty leech, that you're missing out. They have blood the likes of which I've never seen.
Ah, and the heart-stopping bloodsucker. I hope you've changed your mind. My neck is yours, any time.
Can you revert it?
What did you do to me?
Can I give you blood in exchange for some special items?
Not even for the betterment of the alchemical arts the realm over? Not even for that?
Now, where the devil did that bottle go?! My silk! We can't continue without it!

EditorData.NodeContext: 'My silk' as a stand in for 'my stars!' or 'my gods!'

Text.Value: Hold on, my friend, hold on. I do need a sample of that blood before you go. My research will be worthless without it.
You say 'mad'. I say 'extraordinary'. We have that in common, my friend.
And now that you're here, the crown jewel of my research is soon to be faceted. All you have to do is drink Formula Gruna.
You're ready to try Formula Gruna, aren't you?
She said 'no'. You should learn the meaning of the word.
He said 'no'. You should learn the meaning of the word.
They said 'no'. You should learn the meaning of the word.
Now you're happy to leave if I'm uncomfortable? How novel.
Forget it. I saw how you made Astarion feel. I'm done with you.
I trust you haven't forgotten what happened when I drank something she offered? This 'formula' won't be any kinder to you.
I can probably handle a little fire, but I'm not sure about the rest of you.
What will this formula do?

I assure you, the pleasure is mine. This research will skyrocket House Oblodra back to the forefront of scientific thought back home. You know how important it is to protect one's line - with power, ideally, but value works just as well.
I assure you, the pleasure is entirely, entirely mine. This research will skyrocket House Oblodra back to the forefront of drow scientific thought. Indeed, it could protect my line for generations.
If that was all it took to kill me, I'd have died a long time ago.
No, no, no. Does it really need to be said?
It's a deal.
You can really take some heat. I'm impressed.
You're right. Let's have a look.
That seems quite powerful. Thank you.
Why do you need more of my blood so badly?
Formula Gruna?
Ah, my friend. What can I do for you?
And I will keep refusing until the end of time. I'm done bowing to the whims of others.
Leave.
Fie, such cruel words!
How I made him feel? What I propose goes well beyond such frivolities. We are talking about alchemical breakthroughs based on the blood that runs through your veins, my friend!
Oh, darling. If you aren't tadpoled, we have nothing to discuss.

EditorData.logicalname: Araj inside the house, no illithid no hasmet

Text.Value: I think not.
You're mad.
I said no.
My ancestors breathed fire - did you really think that would kill me?
Let me see your wares.
My research will be the greatest breakthrough in the sanguine arts in a century. The Grand Matriarch will have no choice but to restore House Oblodra when I present my findings.
You are so very accommodating.
This is no poison I recognise. Talk - what did you do to me?
Ah, my friend. What can I do for you?
I tremble with anticipation.
And if it does?
Our blood caused that explosion?
But never mind all that. I have tremendously exciting news.
At the very edge of life and death is where one happens upon the true breakthroughs, my friend. That's how I discovered the delicious volatility of the blood sample you gave me.
Ah. I'd so hoped it wouldn't come to this. But I can't let my prize experiment walk out that door. I'd hoped to take a sample with your permission. But I can do without it.
I think not.
I'd like to see your wares.
This won't do, darling. I'll have to take my work back in blood. Lots of it.
I think a firm 'no thank you' is in order. Very firm.
I'll be all right. Let's just get this over with.
No no, my friend - I'm the one impressed by you.
You see, it's your blood that caused the conflagration you just witnessed. Imagine!
I'm afraid your blood is of little interest to me. But perhaps I can interest you in some other items.
But listen to me, rabbitting on about myself when I have you - the prize bleeder - on my very doorstep.
You tricked me. You'll pay for that.
Leave.
All it needs is a spark.
Never say never.
Can I give you more blood in exchange for some special items?
Boh! A pity. But you may change your mind - and if you do, don't hesitate to seek me out. I'll always be happy to see you.
My friend, I had no such intention. You don't know what this means to me - to my research!
You? You ruined my relationship with Astarion!
Oh she doesn't bother me that much. If anything, I pity her.
A potion that makes you explode? Seems a bit drastic.
You really are a fine collaborator.
You heard me the first time, didn't you, darling? I'd like to speak to your tadpoled friend, if you don't mind.

EditorData.logicalname: Araj inside the house, no illithid hasmet

Text.Value: If you'd come inside, we could discuss something far more exciting than drow politics.
I'm glad Astarion isn't here to hear of your vile experiments.
Not if you lead me first!

EditorData.NodeContext: Awkward, A little giddy with excitement.

Text.Value: One source of lethal explosive power in our party is quite enough. It seems ill-advised to add another.
Not today, I'm afraid. I need a nice and juicy sample - take too often, and you drain your specimen dry!
No, give yourself some credit. You mostly ruined it all by yourself.
And, ahh, the heart-stopping bloodsucker. Ever since our last liaison, I haven't been able to get you out of my mind...
I would like to see her dead in a ditch, but I can tolerate this.
Ah - a cosy little spot, isn't it? These four walls have witnessed greater alchemical triumphs than the keep of Urngath Dorrund!

EditorData.NodeContext: You can pronounce the name phonetically/ as makes sense to you

Text.Value: It's a breakthrough in the sanguine arts the likes of which the world has never seen. The Grand Matriarch will have no choice but to restore House Oblodra after I present her with my research.
I'd hypothesised you wouldn't, my friend. And you've proven me absolutely correct.
But! All is far from lost!
Go on and take some.
Let's just leave.
Well, hearing her out won't kill us.
Do not trust anything this woman says. And certainly don't drink anything she offers you.
Never better. Don't mind the mess. I've been doing fascinating things with your blood sample.
Lucky for us all, fate is more powerful than hope.
Don't worry, I can tolerate her.
Oh, marvellous. I've never been so excited for anything in all my days! Just - stand over there. Far over there. And drink up!
I am magic incarnate - it will take more than that to kill me.
I should have known you would turn on me. We might have left the Underdark, but its treachery is never far behind.
Certainly not. But it might do damage to anyone who makes you bleed without your express permission.
I won't be drinking any mysterious formulas today, thanks.
Marvellous!
Forgive the mess. Your blood is far more volatile than I'd anticipated.
YES!

EditorData.NodeContext: Enthusiastically urging the player to drink a potion that makes their blood explode when exposed to air.

Text.Value: My blood caused this explosion?
I'm fine. Let's just get this over with.
A brew so potent, it makes you explode? Perhaps it has some use... though I struggle to see what.
Well yes. Formulae Arkku through Fruak were spectacular failures. But Gruna - Gruna is different. Believe me!
Don't worry - if anything happens, I'll protect you.
I'm dying to speak with them. You will send them my way, won't you? Ta!
I am, yes.
Sigh. Why not.
You... what?! Formula Gruna... the height of my research... you destroyed it?!
You, my friend, have become something... something I once thought beyond achievement.
Erm, are you all right?
Leave.

Synopsis: Dialog with Araj if you find her in Lower City
